title: The Duchess of Cambridge’s new look
text:
She’s known for her demure and sophisticated style, but the Duchess of Cambridge appears to have taken a step back in time at this year’s BAFTAs, sporting a very old-fashioned hair-do on the red carpet. media_camera The Duchess of Cambridge appears to have taken a step back in time. Picture: Gareth Cattermole/Getty Images media_camera The attention was on the royal’s vintage hair up. Picture: Daniel Leal-Olivas- WPA Pool/Getty Images media_camera Kate’s hair was tied back in a large eye-grabbing beehive bun. Picture: John Phillips/Getty Images 
As glamorous as she looked in her figure-hugging Alexander McQueen gown, the attention was less on the dress and more on the royal’s vintage hair-up which was tied back in a large eye-grabbing beehive bun. media_camera The Duchess of Cambridge went for a more traditional look. Picture: Daniel Leal-Olivas- WPA Pool/Getty Images 
While she’s usually commended on her modern fashion sensibility, it seems the Duchess opted to follow in her famous grandmother-in-law’s footsteps, with a very surprising classical look for the event. media_camera It seems the Duchess opted to follow in her famous grandmother-in-law’s footsteps. Picture: Apic/Getty Images 
The style was noticeably similar to how Queen Elizabeth wore her hair back in her younger days. 
It’s a contrast from Kate’s other red carpet looks, which sees the 35-year-old beauty showing off her luscious brunette lox in a more relaxed style. media_camera It’s a contrast from Kate’s regular red carpet looks. Picture: AFP Photo / Pool / Richard Pohle media_camera The royal often shows off her luscious brunette lox in a more relaxed style. Picture: Samir Hussein/Pool/ WireImage
